This paper deals with the analysis of real-world events on social media, specifically Twitter. It involves the study of collective behavior and bursty activity patterns, which are typical topics in the field of social informatics (cs.SI) and social network analysis (cs.SOC). The paper also proposes a methodology for classifying news events based on their intensity of activity, which could fall under the category of data mining (cs.SD) or information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper discusses the prediction of high-activity events, which could involve machine learning (cs.CY) techniques.
